        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
The level 60 Shaman is the king of duels.  Do the math on torpor and you will see it for the overpowered pile of shit that it is.  

Consider, Splurt is ~11dps in PvP, Pyro is ~12dps, Ignite Blood is ~6dps, Pyre is ~26dps.

Chain Touch of Night is 52 dps in PvP. Cost: 405mana.

Torpor heals 50 points per second. Cost: 200 mana.

Chloroblast, when chain cast, heals 71dps. Cost: 175 mana.

First thing the shammmy is going to do is root and then slow your pet.  Pretend the shammy is stupid enough to let you stack all those dots on him and not dispell them.  He can torpor himself and chain cast chloro while you run yourself OOM casting Touch of Night, and live.  Now you have an oom Necro against a Shammy who still has quite a bit of mana. This is a *BEST* case scenario for the Necro.  It's kinda sick when they really go all out what happens to the Necro.

At level 60, the shaman is the king of duels.  All the shammy needs is basic knowledge of his class and a brain.  I hate them :P

-Saleem
Warlock of Xegony
