        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> there should be no reason why a necro should lose to a warrior or a rogue. Warriors and rogues are easy because all you need to do is dot, and let pet attack them and run them around in circles. caster classes can be more difficult. Ive personally killed a lvl 56 chanter at lvl 54, and have killed a lvl 58 cleric at lvl 56, but it all depends on luck, gear and how well you and your oponent are good at dueling. Now im not bragging about killing the above classes, because i too have been owned in a few duels. </P><P>clerics can stun and nuke which is bothersome, but you can get around it by having pet attack and hope to god you get a few openings where you can get off a few dots and lifetaps. </P><P>Chanters are a nasty class to duel. they can charm you or your pet, which from there it can become very nasty. </P><P>Bards are also difficult because of their high resist songs they can play, there aoe damage songs, and also their speed songs.</P><P>You need to be careful withs sks because if they have their HT up, you can die fast.</P><P>Wizzyz........i would suggest you never duel a wizzy if you wanna keep your honor in tack. Wizzies will kill you faster than you can blink.</P><P>Mages are pretty difficult because their pet and your pet would both be engaged and you would have to use lifetap often to keep the mages nukes from getting to ya.</P><P>i dont know much about dueling paladins, rangers, shammies, druids, beastlord, or monks since i have not dueled them much.</P><P>You will never stick fear in higher lvl duels, and root gets resisted a lot and doesnt last long. but basically you just need to have the right spells memed and know how to play your class, and with the right luck you might come out a winner.</P><P> </font></td>
