        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I have been playing on PvP servers since day one. Rallos to Vallon and now on Sullon. I am also a 60 necro and I have fought just about any class out there. Here is my opinion and what I have seen. Gear does have a lot to do with but my opinion is pretty netural.</P><P>Clerics- Forget it you can't kill them they can't kill you type of battle, unless you have all day. With complete heal and the ability to dispel every single dot you have I find them boring and a waste of mana to fight.</P><P>Wizards- If manaburn is up go ahead and find a cleric for a rez. I have had 4k hps and manaskin and still get hit for 6700ppts of dmg from manaburn. Apart from mana burn these guys are easy, dot(vexing)and run. If they stop to dispell the dots deflux or ToN them to death. Most wizards are a sure win even with epic.</P><P>SK,Warriors,Rogues,Paladins- If you are indoors, what the hell are you think.... gate ). If you are outdoors and for some reason die to these guys you have some issues. On major note of these guys, how you buff matters. Dot and run, repeat.... HT does suck ). Rogues I can land to 2 magor dots before they get through Manaskin then just run around. But I have played against some skilled melee(owned me)and my hat goes off to them.</P><P>Rangers- one word dot/deflux kills these guys pretty quick. They are fast and can run but with one dot and defluxing I have had great luck against rangers. BTW if they use trueshot it owns casters.</P><P>Druids- They are worthless against necros I have killed so many of these guys and rarely die. They are fast and can heal but WD sucks and ToN owns them. Also their DD sucks, easy to resists.</P><P>Shamans- I think this is the thoughest match we have They have Malo and awesome dots. Also the are fast and can heal. I try to avoid these guys.</P><P>Enchanters- Same as clerics I don't bother with them.</P><P>Mages/Beastlords- I feel so bad ) fear pet, dot/tap mage, dead. Or root pet, dot/tap mage, dead, Or snare pet, dot/tap mage, dead. Epic pet is different,hard to snare,root, and runs faster then a shaman on scale. Just gate if they have Epic ).</P><P>Bard- ghey</P><P><BR>I Never use my pet )</P><P><BR> </font></td>
